# Frontend Patterns

## Component Architecture

### Server vs Client Components
- **Server Components** (default): pages, layouts, data fetching wrappers
- **Client Components** ("use client"): forms, interactive UI, audio recorder, anything with hooks/state
- Never pass functions as props from Server → Client components
- Use Server Actions for form submissions and mutations

### Component Organization
```
src/components/
  ui/           # shadcn/ui primitives (Button, Input, Card, etc.)
  audio/        # AudioRecorder, Waveform, TranscriptDisplay
  notes/        # NoteEditor, NoteSection, BillingCodes, TemplateSelector
  layout/       # Sidebar, Header, MobileNav, PageWrapper
  common/       # LoadingSpinner, ErrorBoundary, EmptyState, StatusBadge
```

### Component Patterns
```tsx
// Always type props explicitly
interface ConsultationCardProps {
  consultation: Consultation;
  onSelect?: (id: string) => void;
}

// Prefer composition over configuration
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <CardTitle>{title}</CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>{children}</CardContent>
</Card>
```

## State Management

### Zustand Stores (client state)
```
src/stores/
  useAuthStore.ts        # Current user, session
  useRecordingStore.ts   # Recording state, audio levels, connection status
  useConsultationStore.ts # Active consultation, transcript, note
  useUIStore.ts          # Sidebar open, modals, toasts
```

### TanStack Query (server state)
- All API data fetching via useQuery/useMutation
- Query keys follow convention: ['resource', id?, filters?]
- Stale time: 30s for dashboards, 5s for active consultation data
- Mutations optimistically update where safe (e.g., note edits)

## Form Patterns
```tsx
// Every form uses React Hook Form + Zod
const schema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1, "Required"),
  specialty: z.string().min(1, "Select a specialty"),
});

type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;

const form = useForm<FormData>({
  resolver: zodResolver(schema),
  defaultValues: { name: "", specialty: "" },
});
```

## Styling Rules
- Tailwind utility classes only (no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary)
- Medical professional aesthetic: clean whites (#f8fafc), subtle blues, generous whitespace
- Minimum 44px touch targets for tablet use
- Font scale: text-sm (labels), text-base (body), text-lg (headings), text-2xl (page titles)
- Consistent spacing: p-4 (cards), gap-4 (grids), space-y-3 (form fields)
- Status colors: green=finalized, blue=in-progress, amber=needs-review, red=recording

## Page Layout Pattern
```tsx
// Every page follows this structure
export default function PageName() {
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-6 p-6">
      {/* Page header */}
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-medical-text">Page Title</h1>
        <Button>Primary Action</Button>
      </div>

      {/* Page content */}
      <div className="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {/* Content */}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Loading & Error States
- Every data-fetching component handles: loading, error, empty states
- Use Suspense boundaries at the page level
- Skeleton loaders for cards and lists (not spinners)
- Toast notifications for mutations (success/error)

## Accessibility
- All form inputs have labels (not just placeholders)
- ARIA labels on icon-only buttons
- Focus management after modal open/close
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for text
- Screen reader announcements for recording status changes
